## Configuration & Security Notes

- Use `.env` for shared config and `.env.local` for local secrets; `.envrc` enables dotenv loading.
- For security checks, run `bin/bundler-audit` and `bin/brakeman` (also in `bin/ci`).

## Future Patterns

If the application is missing a pattern you wish to implement, check @ARCHITECTURE.md to see if
the implementation has already been defined but not yet adopted. If you introduce a pattern from
ARCHITECTURE.md, move that section to STYLE.md so future agents know it is now in active use.

# Agent Instructions

## Running Commands

All commands (ruby, `./bin/*`) must be prefixed with `mise exec --` to ensure the correct Ruby
version and gems are available. Without this prefix, commands will fail with missing gem errors.

```bash
mise exec -- bin/rspec
mise exec -- bin/rubocop
mise exec -- bin/rails generate migration AddNameToUsers
```

Use tools installed by mise directly when available:

```bash
mise exec -- oxlint app/javascript/controllers
mise exec -- bunx stylelint app/assets/stylesheets/
```
